accessibility.text: Elysium Mons is located at 25N, 213W, in the martian eastern hemisphere. Elysium Mons is one of three large volcanoes that occur on the Elysium Rise the others are Hecates Tholus (northeast of Elysium Mons) and Albor Tholus (southeast of Elysium Mons). The volcano rises about 12.5 kilometers (7.8 miles) above the surrounding plain, or about 16 kilometers (9.9 miles) above the martian datum the \"zero\" elevation defined by average martian atmospheric pressure and the planet's radius.
